HEADWORD: Scooper
<hw>Scoop"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, scoops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The avocet; -- so called because
it scoops up the mud to obtain food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scoot</ent>⟦br⟧
